    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-04T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-04T05:00:00-05:00" n="46"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d46">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6856: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-04T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 4, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 4—7:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>23. On January 30 and February 3 the Tokyo correspondent of the <hi rend="italic"
                        >New York Times</hi> telegraphed analyses of the Sino-Japanese situation
                    that merit attention. I am aware that he has consulted high Foreign Office and
                    other officials as well as businessmen. His information is usually accurate,
                    although in this case he seems not to stress sufficiently the economic aspects
                    of the situation, which may prove to be the determining factor in any
                    arrangement reached in the present conversations.</p>
                <p>The Foreign Office here continues to state that Japan is making no demands on
                    China at the present time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
